description: India's retail boom is shifting beyond metros, with Tier II and III cities now leading organized retail expansion. Rising incomes and evolving consumer tastes for lifestyle experiences are fueling this growth. Cities like Raipur, Vizag, and Bhubaneswar are becoming key hubs, attracting brands and investors eager to tap into new, aspirational audiences.
title: India retail shift: Tier II–III cities powering new phase of real estate growth

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: Delhi Police have busted an international arms smuggling ring with suspected ISI links, arresting four individuals. Sophisticated foreign-made weapons, including Turkiye-made PX-5.7 pistols, were seized, having been smuggled via drones from Pakistan. This significant operation aims to dismantle a network intending to destabilize the region.
title: ISI-linked arms racket busted: 10 foreign pistols, 92 live cartridges seized; smuggled from Pak

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: The International Space Station captured a stunning image of Earth at night. Delhi's bright lights stand out, showcasing its growth. The city is compared to other luminous megacities like Singapore, Tokyo, and Sao Paulo. These images reveal urban development and population growth. Orbital views offer insights into future city expansion and energy use.
title: ISS shares breathtaking night views of world’s brightest cities

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: A Jaipur school faces a CBSE show-cause notice after a Class 4 student died by suicide, reportedly due to 18 months of classroom bullying. The inquiry found the school failed to act on repeated complaints, with the class teacher ignoring the child's distress in her final moments. Safety lapses and a non-responsive grievance mechanism were also highlighted.
title: Jaipur school suicide: Student sought teacher's help 5 times, says CBSE report

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Security forces in Manipur have apprehended four militants from banned groups involved in extortion activities. The arrests, made in Thoubal and Imphal West districts, led to the recovery of weapons, ammunition, and incriminating documents. These operations are part of ongoing efforts amidst the state's persistent ethnic violence.
title: Manipur crackdown: Four militants arrested; men linked to banned groups carried out extortion

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India A captain Jitesh Sharma accepted responsibility for their semi-final loss to Bangladesh in the Rising Stars Asia Cup. The controversial decision to not bat Vaibhav Suryavanshi in the Super Over backfired, with Jitesh and Ashutosh dismissed for golden ducks. Despite a strong start and a late surge, India A narrowly missed out on a tie, ultimately falling short.
title: Revealed! 'That was on me': Jitesh explains choice to bench Suryavanshi in Super Over

author: MANTHAN K MEHTA
description: A passenger's viral video of cooking instant noodles in an AC coach using a household electric kettle has prompted Central Railway to take action. The railway authorities identified the social media user and will initiate proceedings under the Railways Act for misusing railway property and posing a fire hazard.
title: Watch: Passenger cooks noodles in train in electric kettle; Railway fumes

author: TNN
title: Delhi breathes very poor air on 16 of 21 days in November

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India's toss woes continue as Rishabh Pant loses the coin flip to South Africa's Temba Bavuma in Guwahati. South Africa elected to bat first on a pitch expected to favour batters initially. India made two changes, including Sai Sudharsan and Nitish Kumar Reddy, while South Africa bolstered their spin attack.
title: 38th captain, 8th toss lost: Rishabh Pant continues Team India's coin flip woes

author: DEVANSHI MEHTA
description: Police are investigating the suicide of 16-year-old Shourya Patil, who allegedly jumped from a metro station after facing days of humiliation by teachers. His classmates reported threats of expulsion and physical altercations. A suicide note found in his bag details alleged harassment by four teachers, who have since been suspended by the school pending investigation.
title: Delhi boy 'suicide': Police secure CCTV footage showing Class 10 kid 'humiliated'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rishabh Pant stepped in as India’s captain, replacing Shubman Gill, who was ruled out due to a neck injury sustained in the first Test. India also made two more changes, with B Sai Sudharsan and Nitish Kumar Reddy coming in for Gill and Axar Patel.
title: 'His body didn't allow ... ': Rishabh Pant gives major update on Shubman Gill

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: J&K: Pak drone spotted over Ghagwal area; forces sweep area for potential payload

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US government data on October inflation and jobs won't be released due to a record shutdown, leaving the Federal Reserve blind ahead of its December policy meeting.  The Bureau of Labor Statistics confirmed the cancellations, citing an inability to collect essential survey information. This data gap intensifies uncertainty for the Fed as it considers interest rate adjustments.
title: Shutdown fallout: US scraps Oct inflation and jobs figures after data-gathering halt

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Pop culture is abuzz as Sabrina Carpenter reportedly meets with Marvel for the Dazzler role, reigniting debate over Taylor Swift's potential casting. Fans long envisioned Swift as the music-powered mutant, citing her stage presence and pop icon status. While Carpenter offers a fresh take, Swift's connection to Dazzler remains a captivating 'what if' for many.
title: Sabrina Carpenter snubs Swift’s Marvel debut to plan wedding with Travis Kelce

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: Ciara, Kelly Rowland, and La La Anthony revealed Russell Wilson's playful and curious nature in their group chats.  Despite NFL challenges, Wilson actively joins conversations, offering genuine curiosity and honest advice, earning him a valued spot in their trusted circle. His presence brings humor and thoughtful input, strengthening their bond.
title: Ciara jokes about Russell Wilson being nosy during her chats with celebrities

author: SANJEEV VERMA
description: Wing Commander Namansh Syal, a proud son of Himachal Pradesh, tragically lost his life during a Tejas aircraft crash at the Dubai Air Show. Hailing from Kangra district, Syal was a decorated officer with a distinguished career, having trained at Sainik School and the National Defence Academy.
title: Dubai Tejas crash: Who was Wing Commander Namansh Syal? IAF pilot who died in incident

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Veteran actor Himani Shivpuri, who shared screen space with Aishwarya Rai in Hamara Dil Aapke Paas Hai, Inaab, Loot Chale, and Tera Jaadu Chal Gaya, and later acted alongside Abhishek Bachchan in Umrao Jaan, reflected on her experience filming with the former Miss World. When asked about the much-publicised breakup between Aishwarya Rai and Salman Khan supposedly taking place during one of those film shoots, Shivpuri promptly declined to comment.
title: Himani Shivpuri hesitates to address Aishwarya–Salman breakup

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: European nations, particularly Denmark and Norway, are scrutinizing Chinese-made Yutong buses over security fears. Operators worry that 'over-the-air' software updates could allow remote immobilization of the fleet, mirroring concerns over Chinese tech in 5G networks. This potential vulnerability, inherent in connected vehicles, raises geopolitical questions about reliance on foreign manufacturers.
title: Europe has a new fear: China may 'stop its' buses right on roads

author: MOHAMMED AKHEF
description: A 13-year-old student tragically died after jumping from her school's terrace in Jalna. The incident occurred shortly after her grandmother reprimanded her for academic performance and allegedly slapped her. Police are investigating the circumstances surrounding the student's death, with an accidental case registered.
title: Maha 'suicide' shocker: Slapped by her grandma over studies, teen jumps to death

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: NFL's kickoff rule changes face criticism from Donald Trump. Chiefs coach Dave Toub strongly refutes Trump's views. Toub highlights player safety improvements with the new rule. Data shows a significant drop in concussions. The league aims to keep the play exciting and safe for players. Toub believes Trump misunderstands the rule's intent and impact.
title: Chiefs coach says Donald Trump has ‘no idea’ about new NFL kickoff rule

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: In a surprising turn, US president Trump and NYC Mayor Zohran Mamdani met cordially, discussing shared goals for the city's affordability and safety. Despite past animosity, they focused on housing and utility costs, with Trump even defending Mamdani against accusations. This unexpected dialogue signals a potential shift in their relationship.
title: 'Fascist, jihadist next to each other?' Trump-Mamdani grilled at WH meet - watch viral moment

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sanju Samson is thrilled to join Chennai Super Kings for IPL 2026, eager to play alongside his idol MS Dhoni. Traded for Rs 18 Crore, Samson recalled his early admiration for Dhoni and the challenges of meeting him amidst crowds. He expressed immense excitement about sharing the dressing room, breakfast, and practice sessions with the legend.
title: IPL: 'Destiny has got me to play with him'- Samson opens up on leaving RR for CSK

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India batter Smriti Mandhana and composer-filmmaker Palash Muchhal's wedding festivities have commenced with a vibrant Haldi ceremony. Held two days before their November 23 wedding, the event saw Mandhana, adorned in yellow, celebrating with family, friends, and teammates amidst traditional music and yellow decor. The intimate ceremony offered a colourful glimpse into the couple's wedding week.
title: Watch: Smriti Mandhana, Palash Muchhal’s cute Haldi moment melts the internet; fans swoon

author: TOI Education
description: International students in the US are increasingly drawn to STEM disciplines, with a remarkable 57% opting for studies in science, technology, engineering, and math. This surge is fueled by the rising global need for expertise in fields such as computer science and AI, further supported by initiatives like OPT that grant valuable work opportunities post-graduation.
title: Why STEM is the top choice for international students in the US: A deep dive

author: TNN
description: A marine engineer's wife was allegedly assaulted, strip-searched, and publicly humiliated at a Lucknow crockery shop after being accused of theft. She filed an FIR against the shop owner, his family, and employees. The shopkeeper has filed a counter-allegation, claiming the woman and a companion stole plates.
title: ‘Clothes torn’: Marine engineer’s wife ‘strip-searched’ at Lucknow shop
